POTENTIAL RODEO PLAN #1

This plan will simply be a potential plan that I can use. This is not a set plan but it gives me an idea of something I COULD do. This plan will help me to take more control in the game and put me in an ideal jury position at the end. 11th: Kaitan This week I start a war of Me, Kaitan, Blake vs. Zan, Dumbbell, Roy, Hunter, Remi, and Mouse. Shadow will just be kind of there this week. Honestly, I genuinely really want Kaitan out because Kaitan poses a threat to my game in a lot of areas. Kaitan is somebody I really don't trust and I believe would flip if given the chance. I will be spreading small seeds this round to make the sides distrust each other as we go deeper into the merge. 10th: Shadow Sadly, Shadow needs to go here. I can't keep him in much longer, I was considering of eliminating blake here but I think Shadow is a more ideal option for me because Loki can truly expose me if I don't carefully cover my tracks. Shadow can also just kill me if he wanted to with Loki powers and I do not need that. This week should be focused on secretly building him up as a threat. I will especially need to build him up as a threat to Blake, I really want Blake to take out Shadow here. Then overall, I'll just keep playing with deception and strategy. 9th: Blake Sadly, I believe Blake going here is beneficial for my game. If Blake goes here it means that I don't have somebody who will turn the tides of the game against me. This will need to be a blindside where I use my set ability on Blake and I feel it's the best person for my set ability this time around. Another factor about Blake though is I believe he's going to start fighting this week. Then I continue to build a greater distrust between Zan, Dumbbell, and Mouse towards Remi and Hunter. This week should end where Blake goes and I'm in a safe middle position and Leah is only coming to me now because all of her main optional allies are out. 8th: Zan SURPRISE! Somehow, I will get Zan out. How you ask? Well, Leah will have a hunger to get Zan out and I can use some allies to take out Zan. This could even include an anubis play with Remi or a zeus play with Hunter. It will need to be strategic and well coordinated to be done. I really want to connect Leah and Remi by this point where they could be options to the f3 to f4 with. I'll aim this week to focus Mouses and Dumbbells sights on Remi/Hunter while also talking with Roy and boosting him up like he's doing more than he actually is, this can help him believe he doesn't have much reason to flip on me if he so desires.
